  "text": "The Boltzmann equation describes the time development of a six dimensional phase space, which would be very computationally expensive via a finite element approach. Instead, probabilistic approaches based on tracking the trajectories and collisions of representative test particles are a feasible way of solving the Boltzmann equation via statistical means. For description of the movement of neutral particles, the \"Direct Simulation Monte Carlo\" (DSMC) -method [CITATION_1] has been established, while the more general case of neutral and charged particles including self-consistent computation of the electro-magnetic field is referred to as \"Particle-in-Cell Monte Carlo\" (PIC-MC) -method [CITATION_2] .",
